spell /spɛl/

(spelling,spelt,spells) 

1. V-T When you spell a word, you write or speak each letter in the word in the correct order. 拼写; 拼读 

例： He gave his name and then helpfully spelled it. 他说出了他的名字，然后又热心地把它拼读了出来。 

例： How do you spell 'potato?' “”怎么拼写？ 

2. PHRASAL VERB Spell out means the same as . 拼写; 拼读 

例： If I don't know a word, I ask them to spell it out for me. 假如我不知道某个词，我请他们替我拼写出来。 

3. V-T/V-I Someone who can spell knows the correct order of letters in words. 写; 写字 [no cont] 

例： It's shocking how students can't spell these days. 如今学生居然不会写字真让人震惊。 

例： He can't even spell his own name. 他甚至不会写自己的名字。 

4. V-T If something spells a particular outcome, often an unpleasant one, it suggests that this will be the result. 预示 (通常不好的结果) [no cont] 

例： If the irrigation plan goes ahead, it could spell disaster for the birds. 如果该灌溉计划继续的话，这对鸟类可能预示着灾难。 

5. N-COUNT A spell of a particular type of weather or a particular activity is a short period of time during which this type of weather or activity occurs. (某种天气或活动的) 短暂发生期 

例： There has been a long spell of dry weather. 干旱天气已持续很长一段时间了。 

6. V to take over from (a person) for an interval of time; relieve temporarily 在间歇期接替(某人); 暂时换岗 

7. N-COUNT A spell is a situation in which events are controlled by a magical power. 魔 

例： They say she died after a witch cast a spell on her. 人们说一个女巫对她施了魔后她就死了。 

8. N a period or tour of duty after which one person or group relieves another 轮班的时间 

